# üöó Car Diagnostic App

A fullstack car diagnostic platform that connects to vehicles via OBD-II or EV APIs, collects real-time data, and provides predictive maintenance insights using AI.

---

## ‚ú® Features
- **Vehicle Data Collection**: Reads OBD-II error codes, mileage, and real-time parameters.
- **Dashboard UI**: Modern React/Next.js interface for vehicle health, error codes, and alerts.
- **AI Predictions**: Python FastAPI microservice for predictive maintenance (e.g., brake pad wear, catalytic converter efficiency).
- **Service Booking**: Integrated UI for scheduling service appointments.
- **Notifications**: Email/SMS alerts for critical issues.
- **Database Layer**: PostgreSQL for structured data + Redis for caching.

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack
| Layer              | Technology |
|--------------------|------------|
| Frontend           | React, Next.js |
| Backend            | Node.js, NestJS, ASP.NET |
| Database           | PostgreSQL, Redis |
| AI Microservice    | Python (FastAPI) |
| Hardware           | OBD-II dongle / EV API |

---


---

## üöÄ Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v18+)
- Python (3.10+)
- PostgreSQL
- Redis
- OBD-II dongle or EV API access

### Installation
```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/your-username/car-diagnostic.git

# Install frontend dependencies
cd car-diagnostics-next
npm install

# Install backend dependencies
cd backend
npm install

# Install AI microservice dependencies
cd ai-service
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Start frontend
npm run dev

# Start backend
npm start

# Start AI microservice
uvicorn predict:app --reload

